snippet.textDisplay: I like Hearn, I think he's good for boxing, but when it comes to him and AJ I feel that they try to make out he has beaten top opponents, when in reality they have either been past or before their primes, or the referee controls the fight in AJs favour like they did in the Parker fight for example, even in the first Ruiz fight the ref was very reluctant to stop the fight he stopped counting and gave AJ an extra 10-15 seconds. Eddie Hearn is still the best promoter but I refuse to buy into the hype that is AJ.
